WEBVTT

00:00.890 --> 00:02.061
- TOOK SOME PHOTOS?
- MM-HMM.

00:02.100 --> 00:04.648
- THESE ARE PRETTY GOOD, MAX.
YOU OUGHT TO DO PEOPLE.

00:04.690 --> 00:06.783
- I SAY I WANT TO TALK ABOUT
POSSIBLY SELLING THE HOUSE

00:06.830 --> 00:10.038
AND YOU PULL A YEAR-LONG PROJECT
INTO THE DRIVEWAY?

00:10.070 --> 00:12.106
- PEET MIGHT NOT BE
EXACTLY WHO YOU'RE PICTURING.

00:12.150 --> 00:14.789
- HI. YOU MUST BE JULIA.
- HEY.

00:14.840 --> 00:17.217
- OPEN YOUR EYES. I DON'T WANT
YOU TO MAKE THE MISTAKES I MADE.

00:17.250 --> 00:19.810
- YOUR MOM CALLED, LIKE,
TWO OR THREE TIMES.

00:19.840 --> 00:20.943
- SHE'S ANNOYING.

00:20.980 --> 00:21.901
- YOU DON'T KNOW ROCK AND ROLL!
- WHOA, WHOA, HEY.

00:21.950 --> 00:23.804
- I GOTTA TELL THE BAND
I'M DROPPING 'EM.

00:23.850 --> 00:25.806
- GONNA GET THOSE SONGS BACK.

00:25.850 --> 00:28.318
- YOU WANT ASHES OF ROME
TO COME BACK HERE.

00:28.370 --> 00:29.268
- THANK YOU.

00:30.580 --> 00:33.333
- OKAY, DO YOU WANT HEAW
OR LIGHT PEANUT BUTTER?

00:33.370 --> 00:34.678
- YOU ALREADY
MADE MY SANDWICH.

00:34.720 --> 00:36.119
- I DIDN'T MAKE--
- YEAH, YOU DID.

00:36.170 --> 00:38.582
- I DIDN'T MAKE YOUR SANDWICH.
- RIGHT THERE.

00:38.620 --> 00:39.587
- OH, MY GOD,
I DID MAKE YOUR SANDWICH.

00:39.620 --> 00:40.826
WHAT AN IDIOT. OKAY. UM...

00:40.860 --> 00:44.318
- YESTERDAY YOU GAVE ME
TWO THERMOSES. I ONLY NEED ONE.

00:44.350 --> 00:45.442
- WELL, THAT WAS INTENTIONAL,
THOUGH,

00:45.490 --> 00:47.583
BECAUSE I'M REALLY CONCERNED
ABOUT YOUR HYDRATION.

00:47.630 --> 00:49.074
IT'S MY TOP PRIORITY.

00:49.110 --> 00:50.862
- HEY, I CAN'T FIND
HIS BACKPACK ANYWHERE.

00:50.910 --> 00:52.184
ARE YOU SURE YOU BROUGHT IT
HOME FROM SCHOOL YESTERDAY?

00:52.220 --> 00:54.256
- HONEY, I DIDN'T PICK HIM UP
YESTERDAY, YOU PICKED HIM UP.

00:54.290 --> 00:55.109
[knock on door]
- NO, I DIDN'T.

00:55.150 --> 00:55.969
- YES, YOU PICKED HIM UP
FROM SCHOOL.

00:56.020 --> 00:57.112
- HEY, EVERYBODY.
- HEY, UNCLE ADAM.

00:57.160 --> 00:59.799
- SORRY FOR THE INTRUSION.
- NO PROBLEM, NO PROBLEM.

00:59.850 --> 01:01.397
- JUST HAVE SOME MORE
HAND-ME-DOWNS FROM NORA THERE.

01:01.440 --> 01:03.465
- OH, THANK YOU.
- HI, UNCLE ADAM.

01:03.510 --> 01:04.465
- JABBAR,
WHAT'S GOING ON, BUDDY?

01:04.510 --> 01:05.670
- NOTHING.
- COMING IN HOT.

01:05.720 --> 01:06.539
- WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY.
- COME ON, LET'S GET YOUR SHOES.

01:06.580 --> 01:08.093
- YEAH, THAT'S A NUMBER TWO,
I THINK.

01:08.130 --> 01:10.507
- OH, YEAH?
- YEAH, WE GOT A--

01:10.550 --> 01:12.404
- GOT A LITTLE FRESH LOAD THERE?
- WE SURE DO.

01:12.450 --> 01:14.509
- LISTEN TO ME.
I HAVE GOT SOME GREAT NEWS.

01:14.550 --> 01:15.756
WE GOT THE RIGHTS.

01:15.790 --> 01:17.519
- CONGRATULATIONS.
- TO THE SONGS.

01:17.560 --> 01:18.788
- WHAT SONGS?

01:18.830 --> 01:20.138
- TO THE ASHES OF ROME SONGS.

01:20.180 --> 01:21.727
THE THREE SONGS
WE ALREADY RECORDED.

01:21.770 --> 01:23.829
THE LABEL SAID
WE COULD HAVE 'EM.

01:23.870 --> 01:24.905
- YOU GOT THEM
TO GIVE YOU THOSE SONGS.

01:24.940 --> 01:27.761
- YES, I DID.

01:27.810 --> 01:29.766
- WHAT DEAL DID YOU MAKE?
THEY DON'T JUST GIVE SONG--WHOO!

01:29.810 --> 01:31.732
- I MADE A SWEETHEART DEAL.
THAT'S ALL YOU NEED TO KNOW.

01:31.780 --> 01:32.667
- YOU MADE A SWEETHEART DEAL.
- YES, I DID.

01:32.710 --> 01:34.223
- WHAT IS THE SWEETHEART DEAL?

01:34.260 --> 01:37.809
- I SIMPLY TRADED THE STUDIO
TIME FOR THE SONGS.

01:37.850 --> 01:40.603
- THAT WAS 72 BILLABLE HOURS!
- ALL RIGHT, I KNOW, I KNOW.

01:40.650 --> 01:41.810
BUT THESE ARE THE FIRST...
- THEY WERE MY HOURS.

01:41.860 --> 01:43.339
- THREE SONGS ON THE FIRST
ALBUM--WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

01:43.370 --> 01:44.928
- YEAH.

01:44.960 --> 01:47.781
- I SAID, "I'M GONNA GO GET
THE SONGS," YOU SAID, "OKAY."

01:47.830 --> 01:49.479
- BUT I DIDN'T REALLY
THINK YOU WOULD

01:49.520 --> 01:51.545
POSSIBLY BE ABLE
TO PULL IT OFF.

01:51.590 --> 01:53.137
- WELL, THAT WAS YOUR MISTAKE.

01:54.520 --> 01:55.509
- KIND OF.
- LISTEN, YOU SAID--

01:55.560 --> 01:58.313
- BY GIVING AWAY MY LABOR...
- LISTEN TO ME.

01:58.350 --> 01:59.351
- YOU PULLED IT OFF.
- YOU SAID THEY'RE GOOD.

01:59.390 --> 02:01.358
YOU SAID THAT THEY'RE GOOD SONGS
AND HE CAN SING.

02:01.390 --> 02:03.255
- HE'S A GREAT SINGER.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

02:03.290 --> 02:04.109
BUT HE IS INSUFFERABLE,
AND I'M NOT GONNA WORK WITH HIM.

02:04.150 --> 02:06.289
- THIS IS A GOOD THING,
ALL RIGHT?

02:06.330 --> 02:08.912
SO YOU GOTTA MAN UP.
I WANT YOU TO BE EXCITED.

02:08.950 --> 02:11.362
THE LUNCHEONETTE LABEL IS ALIVE
AND WELL. WE'RE MAKING AN ALBUM.

02:11.400 --> 02:14.608
- I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
I WILL MAN UP IF YOU MAN UP.

02:14.650 --> 02:16.857
ALL RIGHT, DEAL MAKER?
DEAL WITH THAT FOR ME.

02:16.890 --> 02:20.929
MAKE A DEAL. MAKE A DEAL
WITH THE HAMPER ON THAT, OKAY?

02:20.960 --> 02:21.927
- I'LL SEE YOU AT WORK.
ALL RIGHT?

02:21.960 --> 02:23.166
[bell rings]

02:23.210 --> 02:26.896
- I KNOW YOU GOT MY NUMBER

02:26.930 --> 02:29.512
- MAX BRAVERMAN,
CEDAR KNOLL YEARBOOK.

02:29.560 --> 02:30.959
- WAIT, MAX, I DON'T
HAVE MY LIP GLOSS ON.

02:31.010 --> 02:31.829
- WE WEREN'T SMILING.
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

02:31.870 --> 02:33.792
PHOTOGRAPHY'S
ABOUT REAL MOMENTS.

02:33.840 --> 02:34.761
- FAKE SMILES
ARE NOT REAL MOMENTS.

02:34.800 --> 02:36.620
- I GOT SOMETHING ON YOU

02:36.670 --> 02:38.558
- MAX BRAVERMAN,
CEDAR KNOLL YEARBOOK.

02:38.600 --> 02:40.636
[shutter clicks]

02:40.670 --> 02:45.505
- YOU KNOW ME
AND MY WEAKNESS

02:45.540 --> 02:49.408
AND YOU KNOW
MY BIGGEST SECRET

02:49.440 --> 02:52.307
STILL I THINK THAT
I GOT SOMETHING ON YOU

02:52.340 --> 02:54.991
- IS HE TAKING OUR PICTURE?
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

02:55.030 --> 02:55.928
- WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?
- MAX BRAVERMAN,

02:55.960 --> 02:57.370
CEDAR KNOLL YEARBOOK.

02:57.410 --> 02:59.378
- STOP IT, GET AWAY FROM ME!
- SHE'S CRYING.

02:59.420 --> 03:00.899
- SO?
- DON'T BE A JERK.

03:00.930 --> 03:02.340
- I'M CAPTURING MOMENTS
FOR THE YEARBOOK--REAL MOMENTS.

03:02.380 --> 03:04.348
- GO AWAY!
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

03:04.390 --> 03:07.245
- GET AWAY FROM ME!
STOP IT!

03:07.290 --> 03:08.973
- JUST LEAVE US ALONE,
FREAK.

03:09.010 --> 03:10.523
- JUST GO AWAY.

03:10.560 --> 03:12.767
- SWEET-EET-EET PERSUASION

03:12.810 --> 03:14.903
I'VE GOT A HARD

03:14.950 --> 03:19.466
REPUTATION

03:19.500 --> 03:21.912
[shutter clicking]

03:21.960 --> 03:23.951
- HEY.

03:23.990 --> 03:25.719
HEY, HEY, HEY, M-MILLIE, LOOK.

03:25.750 --> 03:28.264
THERE SHE IS AGAIN.
SHE'S TAKING PICTURES.

03:28.310 --> 03:29.959
- HEY! HEY!
- ZEEK. ZEEK.

03:30.000 --> 03:30.989
- HEY. [Whistles] HELLO!
- SHE'S NOT BOTHERING ANYONE.

03:31.030 --> 03:32.270
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- HI. HI. I AM SO SORRY.

03:32.310 --> 03:33.379
- SHE'S NOT BOTHERING ANYONE.
- WELL, SHE'S BOTHERING ME.

03:33.420 --> 03:36.753
- I SHOULD'VE INTRODUCED MYSELF.
I'M KAREN FILLMAN.

03:36.800 --> 03:37.892
CORNING REALTY.
- CAMILLE BRAVERMAN.

03:37.940 --> 03:39.862
MY HUSBAND ZEEK.
- NICE TO MEET YOU, ZEEK.

03:39.900 --> 03:41.379
YOU GUYS, THIS PLACE
IS SO GORGEOUS.

03:41.420 --> 03:44.241
I WAS JUST
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD

03:44.290 --> 03:46.520
DROPPING OFF PAPERS
AT THE TAYLORS' PLACE.

03:46.570 --> 03:49.425
- OH, I HEARD THEY SOLD.
- THEY DID. 30% OVER ASKING.

03:49.470 --> 03:51.847
FIVE SOLID OFFERS. I'VE NEVER
SEEN ANYTHING LIKE IT.

03:51.880 --> 03:53.086
THIS PLACE IS A GOLDMINE.

03:53.120 --> 03:55.327
- DID THE TAYLORS HAVE TO DO
A LOT OF WORK TO THEIR HOUSE

03:55.370 --> 03:57.952
BEFORE THEY PUT IT UP
ON THE MARKET?

03:57.990 --> 04:00.367
BECAUSE WE HAVEN'T
DONE ANYTHING IN SO LONG,

04:00.410 --> 04:02.332
AND TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
WE NEED A NEW ROOF.

04:02.380 --> 04:03.472
- SURE, THE TAYLORS' HOUSE
WAS MODERNIZED,

04:03.510 --> 04:06.274
BUT IT DOESN'T HAVE THE CHARM
THAT THIS PLACE HAS.

04:06.310 --> 04:07.402
THIS ONE WOULD SELL
AT TOP OF THE MARKET.

04:07.450 --> 04:10.613
A HANDYMAN SPECIAL LIKE THIS
WOULD GO IN A SECOND.

04:10.660 --> 04:11.513
IF YOU WANT
I COULD TAKE A LOOK,

04:11.560 --> 04:13.482
I COULD MAYBE GIVE YOU
A PRICE RANGE,

04:13.520 --> 04:15.340
GET YOU A BETTER IDEA
OF WHAT IT'S WORTH.

04:15.390 --> 04:17.483
- THAT WOULD BE GREAT.
- NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

04:17.530 --> 04:20.044
WHAT'D YOU CALL THIS,
A HANDYMAN SPECIAL?

04:20.080 --> 04:21.638
- I-I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING
BY IT, MR. BRAVERMAN.

04:21.670 --> 04:23.399
- YEAH, WELL, IT'S GONNA STAY
A HANDYMAN SPECIAL

04:23.430 --> 04:25.739
IF I HAVE ANYTHING
TO SAY ABOUT IT.

04:25.780 --> 04:27.088
NICE MEETING YOU.
SEE YOU LATER.

04:27.120 --> 04:29.327
- SO YOU PLUNGED IT, EH?
- I PLUNGED IT LIKE CRAZY.

04:29.370 --> 04:30.951
- OKAY.
- I'M NOT A PLUNGER.

04:30.990 --> 04:35.051
- [chuckles]
IS THE CLOG VERY VISIBLE?

04:35.100 --> 04:37.546
- NO, NOTHING, TOTALLY--
WATCH YOUR STEP. TOTALLY CLEAN.

04:37.580 --> 04:40.708
- OH. OH. OH, OKAY.
- YEAH. YOU KNOW?

04:40.760 --> 04:42.409
- WE HAD THIS PROBLEM IN 4E
LAST WEEK, AND THIS--

04:42.450 --> 04:44.486
OOPSIE.
- WOW.

04:44.520 --> 04:45.999
- THIS BABY FIXED IT RIGHT UP.
SO I THINK--

04:46.040 --> 04:46.859
- DO YOU NEED HELP?

04:46.900 --> 04:48.037
- YOU'VE COME
TO THE RIGHT PLACE.

04:48.080 --> 04:49.035
- WHAT IS THAT BABY?

04:49.080 --> 04:52.311
- THIS IS A PLUMBING SNAKE.

04:52.360 --> 04:53.930
- IS THAT FOR TOILETS?
- YEAH.

04:53.980 --> 04:55.311
- OKAY.
- AND WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO...

04:55.360 --> 04:56.736
- LOOK AT YOU.

04:56.770 --> 04:57.976
- IS REALLY, LIKE,
WORK THAT CLOG.

04:58.020 --> 04:58.907
- I'D LIKE TO OFFER HELP,
BUT I'M USELESS.

04:58.950 --> 04:59.939
- NO, IT'S OKAY.
[grunts]

04:59.980 --> 05:02.369
GIVE IT A REAL GOOD--
[growls]

05:02.400 --> 05:05.016
- IS THAT TOO HARD?
- REALLY GET IN THERE.

05:05.060 --> 05:06.982
THINK I FELT SOMETHING
MOVE, SO...

05:07.030 --> 05:08.099
- NEED HELP?
- NO.

05:08.130 --> 05:10.883
- 'CAUSE I CAN'T OFFER IT.
- YOU SHOULD BE ALL SET.

05:10.930 --> 05:12.124
[toilet flushes]
HA!

05:12.170 --> 05:14.616
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

05:20.730 --> 05:23.961
- JOB WELL DONE.

05:24.010 --> 05:26.592
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:26.630 --> 05:28.450
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:28.500 --> 05:31.560
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

05:31.600 --> 05:34.012
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

05:34.050 --> 05:36.564
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

05:36.610 --> 05:38.771
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

05:38.820 --> 05:41.084
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:41.130 --> 05:43.644
FOREVER YOUNG

05:43.680 --> 05:45.500
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

05:45.550 --> 05:48.542
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

05:48.580 --> 05:51.140
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

05:51.170 --> 05:52.489
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

05:52.520 --> 05:56.104
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

05:56.140 --> 05:57.380
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

05:57.420 --> 05:59.172
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:59.220 --> 06:02.929
FOREVER YOUNG

06:02.980 --> 06:04.379
MAY YOU STAY

06:04.430 --> 06:07.900
FOREVER YOUNG

06:11.750 --> 06:13.889
- I ORDERED THE SAUSALITOS,
BUT I CAN CANCEL THEM.

06:13.920 --> 06:15.774
SO LET ME JUST MAKE SURE
I HAVE THIS.

06:15.820 --> 06:17.856
YOU WANT ME
TO MOVE THE WINDOWS

06:17.890 --> 06:19.744
SO THEY'RE FACING
SOUTH AND WEST.

06:19.790 --> 06:22.884
OKAY. YUP.

06:22.930 --> 06:23.954
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.855
[sighs]
- PEET WANTS MORE CHANGES?

06:26.900 --> 06:29.892
- YEAH, IT'S PART
OF HER CREATIVE PROCESS.

06:29.940 --> 06:32.727
- [Chuckles] THAT'S VERY NICE
OF YOU TO CALL IT THAT.

06:32.770 --> 06:34.795
- I MEAN, I CAN DO THE WORK,

06:34.840 --> 06:37.172
IT'S JUST HOW MANY TIMES
IS SHE GONNA CHANGE HER MIND?

06:37.220 --> 06:39.211
- WELL, UNTIL YOU PUT
YOUR FOOT DOWN, BABE.

06:39.260 --> 06:41.080
- OKAY, HONEY,
SHE'S AN ARCHITECT.

06:41.120 --> 06:42.803
IT'S NOT LIKE I CAN TELL HER
TO STOP HAVING IDEAS.

06:42.850 --> 06:45.489
- OKAY, BUT YOU CAN
BILL FOR THE EXTRA HOURS.

06:45.540 --> 06:47.633
- THE BID IS THE BID.

06:47.680 --> 06:49.773
- AM I NOT ALLOWED
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT THIS?

06:49.820 --> 06:50.912
- NO, SORRY, I'M JUST--
I'M PISSED.

06:50.960 --> 06:54.123
- OKAY, WELL, I'M NOT GONNA
GET IN THE MIDDLE OF IT,

06:54.170 --> 06:56.684
BUT YOU AGREED TO A JOB
AND THAT JOB IS CHANGING, SO...

06:56.720 --> 06:58.449
PEOPLE LIKE HER
WILL TAKE ADVANTAGE OF YOU.

06:58.480 --> 06:59.299
I KNOW, I'VE BEEN THERE.

06:59.340 --> 07:01.513
- OKAY, WELL,
THE SECOND I REALIZE

07:01.550 --> 07:02.994
SHE'S TAKING ADVANTAGE OF ME,
I WILL TELL HER.

07:03.040 --> 07:05.964
- GOOD.
- GOOD.

07:06.010 --> 07:07.147
- IT'S REALLY GOOD
TO HAVE BOUNDARIES, YOU KNOW?

07:07.180 --> 07:09.592
FROM THE OUTSET.
- MM-HMM.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.689
- I MEAN, WE DIDN'T SEND A FAX
AT THE FIRM WITHOUT CHARGING.

07:11.740 --> 07:13.594
- YEAH,
THIS IS NOT THE FIRM.

07:13.640 --> 07:15.119
THIS IS A TOTALLY
DIFFERENT THING.

07:15.150 --> 07:18.699
- ALL I'M SAYING IS YOU DON'T
WANT TO END UP IN A SITUATION

07:18.740 --> 07:19.729
WHERE YOU'RE COMPLETELY BEHIND

07:19.780 --> 07:21.987
OR YOU'VE COMPLETELY
EATEN INTO YOUR PROFITS

07:22.020 --> 07:23.089
AND YOU HAVE A FAMILY
TO THINK OF.

07:23.130 --> 07:24.813
- YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'LL TALK TO HER.

07:24.850 --> 07:26.909
- OKAY.

07:26.960 --> 07:28.473
YOU CAN FRAME IT
AS A CONVERSATION

07:28.510 --> 07:30.091
ABOUT YOUR CREATIVE
PROCESS TOGETHER,

07:30.130 --> 07:32.098
AND SHE'LL NEVER EVEN KNOW
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT BOUNDARIES.

07:32.140 --> 07:33.061
[cell phone rings]
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

07:33.100 --> 07:35.921
- PEET AGAIN?
- YOUR SISTER.

07:35.970 --> 07:39.690
HEY, SARAH.

07:39.730 --> 07:41.243
YEAH, OKAY.

07:41.280 --> 07:44.078
UM, NO, YOU CAN'T SNAKE IT
THROUGH THE TOILET BOWL.

07:44.110 --> 07:45.839
YOU HAVE TO USE
THE OUTSIDE LINE.

07:45.870 --> 07:46.939
OH, YOU DID.

07:46.980 --> 07:51.633
OKAY.
UH, I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

07:51.670 --> 07:53.843
YOU GOT IT.
- [clears throat]

07:53.880 --> 07:55.290
- HOW DO I SET BOUNDARIES
WITH YOUR SISTER?

07:55.330 --> 07:57.059
- HER YOU JUST HELP.

07:57.090 --> 08:00.059
- WE KNOW THAT THIS HAS BEEN
A ROUGH WEEK FOR YOU GUYS.

08:00.100 --> 08:03.092
- YEAH. I QUIT MY CUSH GRAPHICS
JOB TO RECORD THIS ALBUM.

08:03.130 --> 08:05.018
- LOOK, SCREW THE LABEL, MAN.

08:05.070 --> 08:07.584
THEY TALK A SWEET GAME

08:07.620 --> 08:09.303
STRUTTING OUT
THEIR PIMP A&R GUY

08:09.350 --> 08:11.272
WITH SOME ROCK CREDENTIAL CREDIT
FROM 1940, ALL LIKE,

08:11.310 --> 08:14.199
"I DISCOVERED THE BASS PLAYER
FOR MINOR THREAT,

08:14.250 --> 08:16.036
SO I KNOW WHAT
ROCK AND ROLL IS."

08:16.080 --> 08:17.069
- I THINK MINOR THREAT'S 1980,
BUT YEAH, THAT'S A VALID POINT.

08:17.110 --> 08:19.146
- ALL RIGHT,
LET'S NOT QUIBBLE OVER DETAILS.

08:19.180 --> 08:21.045
- WHATEVER, MAN,

08:21.080 --> 08:23.765
IT'S ALL PART OF THE SAME
KATY PERRY SAUSAGE FACTORY.

08:23.810 --> 08:26.256
I JUST DON'T WANT TO BE A
CREATIVE HOSTAGE ANYMORE, OKAY?

08:26.290 --> 08:27.803
- I GET THAT,
AND WE DON'T WANT YOU

08:27.850 --> 08:29.249
TO BE A CREATIVE
HOSTAGE EITHER,

08:29.300 --> 08:31.985
AND THAT'S WHY WE WANT
TO PRODUCE YOUR RECORD.

08:32.020 --> 08:35.194
OKAY, AND WE WANT YOUR
CREATIVITY TO JUST FLOW FREELY.

08:35.230 --> 08:37.926
JUST FREE FLOW. RIGHT?

08:37.960 --> 08:40.190
- GATES WIDE OPEN.
FULL DELUGE OF CREATIVITY.

08:40.240 --> 08:41.889
- WOULD YOU PLEASE?

08:41.930 --> 08:43.579
- VIVA CREATIVITY.

08:43.620 --> 08:45.167
- THAT'S AWESOME
YOU FLIPPED A BUNCH OF SWITCHES

08:45.210 --> 08:46.131
BACK IN THE DAY.

08:46.180 --> 08:48.034
- MM.

08:48.070 --> 08:48.889
- BUT THIS IS A RECORD,
AND YOU GOTTA PRODUCE IT.

08:48.940 --> 08:51.727
YOU'RE PRODUCING MY RECORD.
- RIGHT.

08:51.770 --> 08:54.216
- WHAT ABOUT THE SONGS
WE ALREADY RECORDED?

08:54.250 --> 08:55.763
- OH, YOU'RE GONNA LIKE THIS.

08:55.810 --> 08:58.768
TELL 'EM ABOUT THE SWEETHEART
DEAL YOU BROKERED.

08:58.810 --> 09:00.801
- I MADE A DEAL
WITH YOUR FORMER LABEL.

09:00.850 --> 09:02.158
IN EXCHANGE FOR THE AMOUNT

09:02.190 --> 09:03.669
THAT THEY OWED
FOR THE RECORDING TIME...

09:03.710 --> 09:04.779
- I.E. MY LABOR.

09:04.820 --> 09:08.369
- WE HAVE THE SONGS.
WE OWN THE SONGS.

09:08.400 --> 09:10.095
AND THAT WAS
A BIG PAYDAY FOR US,

09:10.130 --> 09:12.928
AND I THINK THAT SPEAKS TO
HOW MUCH WE BELIEVE IN YOU GUYS.

09:12.960 --> 09:13.995
- I DON'T KNOW.
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME, MAN.

09:14.030 --> 09:16.544
- DOES IT?
- YEAH.

