15:54.710 --> 15:55.631
WHAT ARE THEY DOING?
- I DON'T KNOW.

15:55.670 --> 15:58.230
I GUESS PHOTOSHOP, RIGHT?

15:58.260 --> 16:00.979
THAT'S A GOOD THING FOR--
- THAT'S A JOKE, PHOTOSHOP.

16:01.020 --> 16:02.339
- YOU DON'T USE--

16:02.370 --> 16:03.337
- PHOTOSHOP SUCKS, OKAY?

16:03.370 --> 16:05.474
EVERYBODY DOES IT,
BUT IT'S NOT PHOTOGRAPHY.

16:05.510 --> 16:09.640
PHOTOGRAPHY IS IN THE DARKROOM,
MAKING PHOTOS LIKE THIS ONE.

16:09.690 --> 16:11.544
LOOK AT THIS. THIS IS GOOD.

16:11.590 --> 16:14.036
I MEAN, IT'S REALLY GOOD.

16:14.070 --> 16:17.176
I MEAN, SUBJECT MA'ITER ASIDE,
WHICH IS A KNOCKOUT,

16:17.210 --> 16:18.552
IT'S GOT COMPOSITION,
IT'S GOT DEPTH,

16:18.590 --> 16:20.478
GREAT USE OF LIGHT.

16:20.530 --> 16:23.283
THAT KID IS A PHOTOGRAPHER.

16:23.320 --> 16:28.087
HE SHOULD BE TAKING PICTURES.
SHOULDN'T BE ON LAYOUT.

16:33.570 --> 16:36.459
- SO CAN WE GET THAT
LEVELED

16:36.510 --> 16:38.569
BY NEXT l'JTHURSDAY?

16:38.610 --> 16:41.056
ALL THIS. YEAH.
- YEAH. GREAT.

16:41.100 --> 16:42.647
I REALLY WANT TO GET STARTED
ON THE FOUNDATION.

16:42.690 --> 16:43.714
WHAT ARE THOSE?

16:43.760 --> 16:46.445
- THAT'S THE WINDOWS.
- RIGHT.

16:46.480 --> 16:49.199
HOLD THE BEAT ON THEM.
- THE--THE--

16:49.240 --> 16:50.719
THE WINDOWS YOU CALLED ME
ABOUT THIS MORNING.

16:50.760 --> 16:52.728
FACING WEST AND SOUTH.
- MM-HMM. NO, I KNOW.

16:52.770 --> 16:54.169
IT'S JUST THERE'S
A BETTER WAY

16:54.220 --> 16:55.790
TO INTEGRATE THE LIGHT
AND THE PRIVACY HERE.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.831
SO I JUST WANT
TO TAKE ONE MORE LOOK

16:57.870 --> 16:59.838
BEFORE WE SET THAT IN STONE.

16:59.880 --> 17:01.529
- OKAY, UM...

17:01.570 --> 17:03.458
YOU KNOW, I'D LOVE TO HAVE
A CONVERSATION AT SOME POINT

17:03.500 --> 17:05.775
ABOUT OUR CREATIVE PROCESS
TOGETHER.

